&lt;p&gt;If you’re ready to see your impact and unlock incredible career growth opportunities, join us, and build real world value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;THE WORK&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Ripple intern, you will work on challenges that impact our mission and shape our company. With support from your team, access to learning and development resources, and opportunities for fun along the way, our program will give you the foundation to start your career journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ripple Impact is helping to develop a more scalable, sustainable, ethical and inclusive global blockchain ecosystem by supporting education, research and technical innovation in blockchain and FinTech through its flagship university partnerships program, the University Blockchain Research Initiative (UBRI). UBRI now includes more than 55 universities from 26 countries worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Research Associate for Ripple Impact, you will play an instrumental role in helping to grow UBRI’s program, through both employee driven efforts and collaboration with leading universities. This is a rare and exciting opportunity to be involved in delivering an innovative program at a phenomenal place to work with the potential to have a tremendous, positive impact globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the head of the University Blockchain Research Initiative to ensure all partnerships are adequately supported and highly productive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze interim reports and present findings to highlight success metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor progress of research projects and track major developments and milestones of UBRI to represent and share program success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and support subject matter experts and University alma mater internally and connect to partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a champion for UBRI inside Ripple’s culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate global employees on regional partner highlights and connect them to opportunities to get involved with local faculty and students on projects or events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
